546-## 16. Open Questions / Deferred Decisions
547-
548-The following are intentionally left for the writing-plans phase or for future specs. They are not blocking spec acceptance.
549-
550-1. **Snapshot equality algorithm.** §9.3 calls for a fast deep-equal with best-effort `firstDifferingPath`. Concrete algorithm (recursive walk vs canonical-JSON hash + targeted diff) chosen during implementation. JSON-canonical hashing is appealing for speed but loses the path-of-first-divergence information. Implementation will likely use recursive walk with short-circuit; benchmark on the long-capture smoke test will validate throughput target.
551-2. **Versioning policy for breaking bundle changes.** When `schemaVersion` bumps to 2, do we ship a migrator (`migrate(bundle, fromVersion, toVersion)`) or simply reject older versions? Decision deferred to the first time a bump is needed.
552-3. **Default `snapshotInterval` of 1000.** Validated by the long-capture smoke test in §13.2. May be tuned based on representative bundle sizes.
553-4. **Async vs sync sink methods.** §8 declares both; the recorder awaits sink calls so both work. Whether to expose the sync/async distinction in the type system (`SyncSessionSink` vs `AsyncSessionSink` brand types) is an implementation-phase decision.
554:5. **`ReplayerConfig.worldFactory` ergonomics.** Requiring callers to provide a factory that re-registers components/validators/handlers/systems is necessary because those can't be serialized. The spec doesn't define a higher-level helper that captures factory output for re-use; that's a candidate quality-of-life addition in a follow-up.
